abstract = {Healthcare has undergone significant changes in recent decades to incorporate new technology and meet evolving needs of the people and the community. This shift has replaced traditional methods like prescription pads and patient charts with digital screens and software. The adoption of these advancements has had a positive impact on patient outcomes and the number of lives saved. It has been recognized that healthcare, including nursing, is experiencing transformative changes due to the presence of artificial intelligence (AI) and robotics systems. These digital technologies have a profound global influence on nursing, emphasizing the importance for nurses to excel both clinically and technologically. Virtual reality (VR) is a form of simulation that utilizes advanced equipment and augmented reality (AR) interventions. VR simulations offer nursing students a valuable opportunity to practice high-risk interventions on virtual patients, allowing them to gain experience without posing any risk to patient safety. AR holds significant promise in the field of education, particularly in medical and nursing education. This is due to its unique capability to seamlessly blend virtual objects with the real world, enhancing simulations and creating a more realistic and immersive learning experience. By integrating virtual elements into the physical reality of users, AR has the potential to revolutionize medical and nursing education by providing students with hands-on interactive training opportunities that closely resemble real-life scenarios. This technology can enhance the understanding and retention of complex medical and nursing concepts, improve diagnostic skills, and facilitate practical learning in a safe and controlled environment. The integration of AR in medical and nursing education has the potential to greatly benefit students and ultimately contribute to the advancement of healthcare. Computer-assisted procedures and surgeries have taken its place in healthcare industry. With the increasing prevalence of robotic surgery, surgeons are faced with the challenge of enhancing and maintaining their skills while ensuring patient safety. Robotic surgery offers several advantages, including faster recovery times, lower complication rates, reduced blood loss, and the restoration of site-specific functions. In addition, telehealth and health informatics have been well accepted in the healthcare industry which assist in delivering various healthcare services remotely. Telehealth includes remote patient monitoring, interventions, education, patient follow-ups, data collection, pain management, and innovative care approaches. One emerging role for nurses in telehealth is telephone triage, which utilizes electronic information and communication technologies to provide healthcare support when distance separates the participants. Through telehealth, nurses excel in providing long-term wellness, self-management, and remote healthcare for their patients which involves offering consultations and treatments using digital platforms. Health informatics refers to the application of the information technologies in the healthcare field to enhance healthcare and overall health of the population. With advancements in technology, the collection, analysis, and utilization of healthcare data have become more effective. In nursing practice, informatics has had a significant impact on documentation. Traditional methods such as paper charts and handwritten notes have been replaced by easily accessible electronic health records and other systems that store and update patients’ medical history. Through electronic charting, nurses can access information and utilize it to improve patient care. Additionally, these medical records can be accessed by all medical professionals involved in the patient’s care, both internally and externally. Health informatics also assists nurses in providing the best possible care by tracking staff shortages, workflow, and facilitating communication within the team to enhance processes without experiencing burnout. Determining the most effective evidence-based practices also involves the use of health informatics, as analyzing collected data on patient care and outcomes helps determine the best care for future patients. Evolution of digital health impacts the future of our healthcare industry.}
